West of Mocksville / Mile Marker 162 to 168 Both Directions. Beginning Monday August 2 2021 eastbound traffic will be maintained in a single lane just west of Exit 168 then will access the median via a crossover and be put into a single head-to-head pattern on the westbound lanes.&nbsp; Once past the US 64 overhead bridge eastbound traffic will be redirected back across the median to resume normal traffic flow approximately 1 mile east of US 64.&nbsp; During this period the exit and entrance ramps for I-40 eastbound will also be closed at Exit 168.&nbsp; Westbound traffic will continue to be in a shorter single lane pattern beginning 1 mile east of Exit 168.&nbsp; This new configuration should be in place for approximately 60 days.&nbsp; The closure is necessary to safely perform pavement repairs on I-40 install drainage make concrete repairs to the existing bridge substructure and concrete pavement slab replacements on the ramps to US 64.&nbsp;
